HEADWORD: Picador
<hw>Pic`a*dor"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.]</ety>
<def>A horseman armed with a lance, who in a bullfight receives the
first attack of the bull, and excites him by picking him without
attempting to kill him.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Picamar</ent>⟦br⟧
